      {
        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "The patient's presentation is concerning for possible musculoskeletal back pain, potentially exacerbated by recurrent strep throat episodes, which may be contributing to glomerular nephritis. Further investigation is warranted to rule out these possibilities.\nPlan\nI am ordering a CT scan to evaluate the back pain and to investigate the recurrent strep throat episodes. I am also referring the patient to an ENT specialist to consider a tonsillectomy if indicated. I am ordering a comprehensive laboratory panel including a lipid panel, UA, CMP, CBC, and Vitamin D to assess his overall health and identify any abnormalities. I have scheduled a follow-up appointment in one week to review the results and discuss further management strategies. The patient should return to the clinic if symptoms persist or worsen.",
